    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Polypeptide-110 is a single chain recombinant human peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is a synthesized copy of the human gene which codes for Fibroblast Growth Factor 5 Isoform 2 Precursor used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 268 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
